# vim
    copy .vim and .vimrc file to ~/ and you are done!

# sublime text
    copy preference, open sublime editor, get preference option, paste and save
    Open sublime, go to In the menu bar, click on Tools, go to Build Systems, then click on New Build System. A window will appear. Now, paste the following codes there erasing the whold document and save it with any name you like, but don't erase .sublime-build from that!

